<h4>
    The Nucleus
</h4>

<p>
    At the center of each atom is the <strong>nucleus</strong>.
    The nucleus contains protons and neutrons. The neutrons are not charged
    and therefore have no effect on electrostatic forces.
    The protons are positively charged, with each proton having a charge of +1 elementary charge,
    or +e.
    Therefore, the nucleus itself is <emph>positively charged </emph>.
</p>

<p>
    Every atom is an atom of a particular element, and each element has an <strong>atomic number</strong>,
    which you can look up on any periodic table of elements.
    The atomic number of an atom gives the number of protons in the nucleus of that atom.
</p>

